	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64587827"><p>People in need do actually spend money on improving their situation. This has been pretty consistently show before, e.g. <a href="https://www.bbc.com/worklife/article/20200624-canadas-forgotten-universal-basic-income-experiment" title="bbc.com">https://www.bbc.com/worklife/a...</a> [bbc.com]</p><p>Considering how much we spend on all sorts of shit, I wish we'd invest into larger scale experients to help drive policy in a scientific manner rather than just going by vibes.</p></div>
