		<div id="comment_body_64587973"><p>Yeah I think there's a core difference as well as giving for example a struggling, working family a UBI versus giving a homeless or disabled person a UBI.  UBI tries to fix one problem and one problem only: a lack of income.   The former group usually is usually assisted with that issue and as you mentioned will generally spend that money on needs.</p><p>The latter group has underlying core problems that are not solved by income, at least not yet, it's just shuffling their core issues around for a little while but<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
