	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64588807"><p><div class="quote"><p>Nobody's forcing you to participate. If you really hate civilisation that much, you can leave it &amp; go &amp; live in the wilderness for as long as you like. Nobody will bother you &amp; it's free of charge.</p></div><p>This is a key point.  The ideology of "taxation is theft" is Newspeak.  In reality, the refusal to participate in society-wide taxation is the real theft because such zealots never intend to deprive themselves of the communal benefits of public taxes and budgets.  They just figure that they will be able to use public roads, schools, libraries, police/fire departments, militaries, etc. for free.  Someone else will pay for those services.  That is truly theft.</p><p>Of course, we should keep in mind that opposing specific taxes and budgets is different from the ideological trope that all taxation is evil.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64588807">
